benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/catalog - Delete all versions for a per tenant catalog

covered: Valid Deletion scenarios demonstrated (TC01, TC02, TC05, TC08, TC15) with 204 responses and post-deletion state checks
Authorization/header handling covered (missing header TC03/TC14, invalid token TC04, extra headers TC08, header validation TC07, optional headers TC02)
Error handling coverage (400/401 for header issues, 404 for non-existent tenant, 500 for internal errors) as shown in TC03, TC04, TC06, TC09
Non-Existent Resource handling (non-existent tenant TC06; no catalog versions TC05)
Data integrity coverage (TC12 ensures no orphaned references after deletion)
Concurrency coverage (TC13 tests concurrent DELETE requests and system consistency)
Security testing (TC11 addresses injection/malicious header input)
Request body ignore behavior (TC15 confirms DELETE ignores request body)
gaps: Pagination behavior for GET listing after deletion is not explicitly tested beyond empty/404 outcome (no dedicated pagination tests for large datasets)
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios on rapid consecutive DELETE requests are not covered
Caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control headers) is not tested
403 Forbidden scenarios (distinguishing 403 vs 401) are not explicitly covered
Soft-delete semantics (whether deletions are reversible or marked as deleted vs hard delete) are not addressed
recommendations: Add explicit GET pagination tests for catalog listings when data exists to verify correct paging behavior
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests for DELETE requests to validate behavior under high load
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on GET/DELETE responses
Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden test case to cover authorization with insufficient permissions
Add tests to verify soft-delete semantics if the system supports non-permanent deletion or cascade behavior
